This paper deals with the problem of online action detection in video streams, which involves analyzing and recognizing human actions in real-time. This problem is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) as it requires the development of algorithms and models that can learn to recognize actions from video data. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of various techniques such as feature extraction, classification, and evaluation, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.RO, in that order.
